      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/65/1",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : «فِي اَلَّذِي عَلَيْهِ اَلْمَشْيُ إِذَا رَمَى اَلْجَمْرَةَ زَارَ اَلْبَيْتَ رَاكِباً»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2790 - Al-Husayn ibn Sa‘id narrated from Isma‘il ibn Hammam al-Makki, from Abu al-Hasan al-Ridha (as), from his father (as), who said: Abu Abdullah (as) said:\n\"For someone obligated to walk [during the Hajj rituals], if they have thrown pebbles at the Jamrah, they may visit the Kaaba (for tawaf) while riding.\""
        ]
      }
    },
